@node section1 "What is JZRAW DL?"

                       @{b}Disclaimer:@{ub}

I accept no responsibility in the use and causes of this software whatsoever.
By using this software you agree to this term!

@{b}Liscence:@{ub}

You are free to do what you want with this software, copy it, distribute
it, eat it or whatever. However you must not change the software in any way
except crunching or archiving or similar activites and you must not claim
ownership of the software. Although this software may be distributed the
Copyright still remains with the Author - Ian Chapman. 

                       @{b}What is it:@{ub}

A RAW download is downloading a file which is not online on the BBS. When run,
it opens a requestor on the workbench screen and the Sysop selects the file to
download. The file is then displayed on the BBS screen and you are asked if
you want to continue. After download you are asked if you have anything
else you want to download. I think this RAW Download door is better than most in
it's choice of requestors. It uses the REQ requestors instead of the old
ARP or ASL requestors. Other RAW download doors don't give you the option
to do another download, they just throw you back onto the BBS.

If you want a door that will allow your users (and/or Co-Sysops) to enter a
pathname and RAW download a file without the Sysop having to interact then
try Remote RAW Download by Ian Chapman. Available from the Jelly Zone BBS
01325 321172 9pm - 8am.

@endnode

@node section3 "Installation on MAXs BBS"

                  @{b}Installation on MAXs BBS@{ub}

Setting it up is easy, just use the MAXs Function 34 for executing an
external door and enter the filename. The door can be stored anywhere you
like but a recommened path and filename is "Doors:JZRawDL/JZRawDL".

It should look similar to this from the MAXs menu  configuration Grid:-

Key:   Function:   Extra:   Lo Acc:    Hi Acc:   Filename/Name/Dest/Path

 R        34         0       10000      10000     Doors:JZRawDL/JZRawDL


It is recommended that you give a Lo Access of 10000 because this door
can only be operated from the local terminal. If a remote user runs
the door and the Sysop is not around, the BBS will hand until someone
at the remote terminal cancels the Requestor.

Requirements:

This door works 100% with MAXsBBS 1.54, it is alomost certain that it'll
work with previous and later versions.

Although this door was paragon based, I don't know if it's paragon
compatible. Try it anyway and if it works then that's your good fortune.

You must have in your LIBS: drawer...

Req.library   

@endnode

